<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1081,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1081,1107]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Medium sized worms with numerous chaetae (up to 
<quantity box="[864,920,1081,1107]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="16.0">16 in</quantity>
ventral bundles) and unsegmented tails. Short and slightly sigmoid hair chaetae present or absent. Lateral wings on crotchet chaetae present or absent. Vasa deferentia usually about as long as atrium, with uniform width, connected to apical end of atrium. Atria globular to tubular in shape, laterally joined by a solid, single prostate gland through a short stalk. Protrusible, true penes usually present without cuticular sheaths or eversible pseudopenes. Loose sperm masses in spermathecae, not forming spermatozeugmata. Coelomocytes sparse or absent. Duplication and forward shift of genital organs often occur. Single embryo in cocoon. Dwelling in mud tubes. The diagnosis is modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Brinkhurst, R. O." box="[1071,1275,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="444 - 625" refId="ref19049" refString="Brinkhurst, R. O. (1971) Part 2. Systematics, 8. Family Tubificidae. In: Brinkhurst, R. O. &amp; Jamieson, B. G. M. (Eds.), &quot; Aquatic Oligochaeta of the World &quot;. Oliver and Boyd, Edinburgh, pp. 444 - 625." type="book chapter" year="1971">Brinkhurst (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hrabe, S." box="[1286,1436,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 167" refId="ref20077" refString="Hrabe, S. (1981) Vodni malostetinatci (Oligochaeta) Ceskoslovenska. Acta Universitatis Carolinae. Biologica, 1979, 1 - 167." type="journal article" year="1981">HrabÄ› (1981)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Finogenova, N. P. &amp; Arkhipova, N. R." box="[199,588,1333,1359]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="7 - 15" refId="ref19862" refString="Finogenova, N. P. &amp; Arkhipova, N. R. (1994) Morphology of some species of the genus Aulodrilus Bretscher. Hydrobiologia, 278, 7 - 15. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 011 - 0842 - 3 _ 2" type="journal article" year="1994">Finogenova and Arkhipova (1994)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1081,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1369,1395]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Brinkhurst, R. O." box="[324,527,1369,1395]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="444 - 625" refId="ref19049" refString="Brinkhurst, R. O. (1971) Part 2. Systematics, 8. Family Tubificidae. In: Brinkhurst, R. O. &amp; Jamieson, B. G. M. (Eds.), &quot; Aquatic Oligochaeta of the World &quot;. Oliver and Boyd, Edinburgh, pp. 444 - 625." type="book chapter" year="1971">Brinkhurst (1971)</bibRefCitation>
listed three diagnostic characters of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bretscher" authorityYear="1899" box="[1066,1184,1369,1395]" class="Clitellata" family="Randiellidae" genus="Aulodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1066,1184,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Aulodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by which he afforded subfamilial rank: 1) prostates attached to atria by broad bases, 2) sperm in bundles (masses) in spermathecae, 3) coelomocytes absent. Subsequently 
<bibRefCitation author="Giani, N. &amp; Martinez-Ansemil, E. &amp; Brinkhurst, R. O." box="[565,780,1441,1467]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="17 - 20" refId="ref19916" refString="Giani, N., Martinez-Ansemil, E. &amp; Brinkhurst, R. O. (1984) Revision du statut taxonomique des Aulodrilinae (Tubificidae, Oligochaeta). Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Toulouse, 120, 17 - 20." type="journal article" year="1984">
Giani 
<emphasis box="[637,696,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">et al.</emphasis>
(1984)
</bibRefCitation>
corrected the first feature, because prostate glands of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Piguet" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Clitellata" family="Randiellidae" genus="Aulodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pluriseta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">A. pluriseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bretscher" authorityYear="1899" box="[308,451,1477,1504]" class="Clitellata" family="Randiellidae" genus="Aulodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="limnobius">
<emphasis box="[308,451,1477,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">A. limnobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are stalked on the atrium like those of 
<taxonomicName box="[900,1031,1477,1503]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tubificinae">Tubificinae</taxonomicName>
, and they invalidated the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[151,296,1513,1539]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aulodrilinae">Aulodrilinae</taxonomicName>
. At the genus level, along with other two characters listed above, short vas deferentia, globular or cylindrical atria, large eversible pseudopenes, and unsegmented posterior ends have been used as diagnostic characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Brinkhurst, R. O." box="[159,347,1585,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="444 - 625" refId="ref19049" refString="Brinkhurst, R. O. (1971) Part 2. Systematics, 8. Family Tubificidae. In: Brinkhurst, R. O. &amp; Jamieson, B. G. M. (Eds.), &quot; Aquatic Oligochaeta of the World &quot;. Oliver and Boyd, Edinburgh, pp. 444 - 625." type="book chapter" year="1971">Brinkhurst 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hrabe, S." box="[360,496,1585,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 167" refId="ref20077" refString="Hrabe, S. (1981) Vodni malostetinatci (Oligochaeta) Ceskoslovenska. Acta Universitatis Carolinae. Biologica, 1979, 1 - 167." type="journal article" year="1981">HrabÄ› 1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Finogenova, N. P. &amp; Arkhipova, N. R." box="[509,865,1585,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="7 - 15" refId="ref19862" refString="Finogenova, N. P. &amp; Arkhipova, N. R. (1994) Morphology of some species of the genus Aulodrilus Bretscher. Hydrobiologia, 278, 7 - 15. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 011 - 0842 - 3 _ 2" type="journal article" year="1994">Finogenova &amp; Arkhipova 1994</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Finogenova, N. P. &amp; Arkhipova, N. R." box="[886,1275,1585,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="7 - 15" refId="ref19862" refString="Finogenova, N. P. &amp; Arkhipova, N. R. (1994) Morphology of some species of the genus Aulodrilus Bretscher. Hydrobiologia, 278, 7 - 15. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 011 - 0842 - 3 _ 2" type="journal article" year="1994">Finogenova and Arkhipova (1994)</bibRefCitation>
emphasized a forward shift of reproductive organs and multiplication of gonads as diagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bretscher" authorityYear="1899" box="[1195,1313,1621,1647]" class="Clitellata" family="Randiellidae" genus="Aulodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1195,1313,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Aulodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1081,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
It is reasonable to regard the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[633,775,1657,1683]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aulodrilinae">Aulodrilinae</taxonomicName>
invalid and to maintain the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bretscher" authorityYear="1899" box="[1153,1271,1657,1683]" class="Clitellata" family="Randiellidae" genus="Aulodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1153,1271,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Aulodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[189,321,1693,1719]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tubificinae">Tubificinae</taxonomicName>
. Among 
<taxonomicName box="[423,554,1693,1719]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tubificinae">Tubificinae</taxonomicName>
, lateral expansions of somatic chaetae occur only in this genus; however, not all congeners have this feature, and species also vary in expression of the other characters listed above. The genusdiagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bretscher" authorityYear="1899" box="[424,542,1765,1791]" class="Clitellata" family="Randiellidae" genus="Aulodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[424,542,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Aulodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are evaluated in the &quot;Discussion&quot;.
</paragraph>
